Almost no one knows about the unlikely friendship between Arno Breker and Salvador Dali.

Dali said that the only sculptor who he wished to have a portrait made by was Breker - and the latter created this piece of him, combining Dali's extravagant looks with his specific style.

The thing about Breker is that most misunderstand his works and believe that he tried to imitate classical sculpture (and failed) in a very bourgeoisie manner. In reality, his art is far closer than that of Dali, closer to expressionism. Salvador, in his genius, could understand.

Dali himself was very much a "Chad". His diary is an amazing book, it honestly felt almost like a spiritual text and might have infected me with schizophrenia when I read it. He has great depth both to his ideas/works and his life. His face reflects this.

Even his own scholars are very often unable to understand him, he had a very unique thought process, the logic, by which he was functioning, does not at all resemble ours. He knew that he was different than other people. I am literally unable to express it, you gotta read him.

Reading some parts of Salvador Dali's diary has been the only thing that has "shaken" my Christian faith. I read it in a state of isolation and it brought me to deep liminal states, disgust, ecstasis, orgasm. He knows of another world, that he himself has created.
He was possessed by a demon for a time, he had an exorcism done. Have you read about this? Afterwards he became a Christian, he made a painting to the monk (or was it a priest?) who exorcised him.

Like this is the thing about Dali, he operated under his own logic. We are literally unable to understand it. We do not live in the same world as him. He is closer to a demigod or a Lovecraftian creature than to a regular man. He had a logic of his own, different to ours.

And yet, under that logic, he managed to reach the truth of Christianity. This proves that Christ truly transcends above the concept of logic, that He can be reached through any system of knowledge. This is very hard to properly express with words/explain, I feel very limited.
